commit.message: Add support for Python 3.12

Fix tests under Python 3.12

There's a test that checks whether `import setup` works; our setup.py
requires setuptools.

Before Python 3.12, setuptools was preinstalled in all the virtualenvs.
Virtualenv 20.23.0 changed this:

  - Do not install wheel and setuptools seed packages for Python 3.12+.

See https://github.com/pypa/virtualenv/issues/2487 for details and
rationale.

Remove obsolete workaround

I don't see any deprecation warnings on Python 3.7 or 3.11 any more.
Fix GitHub Actions badge

Quick workaround for ToC overlapping text

I don't grok display: flex TBH.  I wonder if this breaks something else.

Python 3.11 optimizes away creation of Python frame objects, so these
branches are not getting executed as much as they used to be.

commit.message:
Make Python graphviz package dependency optional

Move the Python graphviz package dependency into `ipython` extra
in order to make it optional.  The code already assumes it optional,
and the tests do not need it at all, so this avoids it being
unnecessarily forced for everyone.
